<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Suggestion for code sample to illustrate partialLoop usage with object model; although the docs appear comprehensive now my own code is working, they really didn't when I was having trouble with it!</p>

<p>So, to list all bugs with status new, together with who they were reported by, you could use code like:</p>

<p>In the controller:
$bugsTable = new Bugs();
$bugsRowset = $bugsTable-&gt;fetchAll(array('bug_status = ?' =&gt; 'NEW'));
$this-&gt;view-&gt;bugsRowset=$bugsRowset;
$this-&gt;view-&gt;partialLoop()-&gt;setObjectKey('bugsRow');</p>

<p>And in the view script:
</p><ul><li>
&lt;?=
    $this-&gt;partialLoop('partial.phtml',$this-&gt;bugsRowset);
?&gt;
</li></ul><p>And partial.phtml
</p> 
&lt;?=$this-&gt;bugsRow-&gt;description; ?&gt;
reported by
&lt;?=$this-&gt;bugsRow-&gt;findParentRow('Accounts')-&gt;account_name; ?&gt;

    </div>
</div>

